</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF96FF99E9FBFD1EFE6BFC4F" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF96FF99E9FBFD1EFE6BFC4F" blockId="9.[151,1437,546,1219]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99E9FBFD1EFED4FD2F" bold="true" box="[199,321,654,679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The embolic disc and embolus of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99EBF6FD1FFCDFFD2F" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[714,842,654,679]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulvinus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99EBF6FD1FFCDFFD2F" box="[714,842,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. pulvinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF96FF99EA6DFD1EFC39FD2F" box="[849,940,654,679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99EA6DFD1EFC39FD2F" bold="true" box="[849,940,654,679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99ED88FD1FFAFFFD2E" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1997" box="[1204,1386,655,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinensis">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99ED88FD1FFAFFFD2E" box="[1204,1386,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. argentinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the short dPED points prolaterally and the vPED points retrolaterally. However, the vPED of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99ED8EFD23FAA1FD43" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1202,1332,690,715]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulvinus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99ED8EFD23FAA1FD43" box="[1202,1332,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. pulvinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF96FF99EC03FD22FA09FD43" box="[1343,1436,690,715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99EC03FD22FA09FD43" bold="true" box="[1343,1436,690,715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
arises from prolateral border of the embolic disc (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99EB82FD46FC95FD67" box="[702,768,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,212,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1393,193,1791]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Amphidraus pulvinus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; ITA, intermediate tibial apopHysis; RSDL, retrolateral sperm duct loop; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. Black arrows indicate pillow-like membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855457/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
C), while in 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99EAB7FD47FBAAFD66" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1997" box="[907,1087,727,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinensis">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99EAB7FD47FBAAFD66" box="[907,1087,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. argentinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it arises from the middle of the distal portion of the disc (see 
<bibRefCitation id="CA3D4B7EFF96FF99E8D1FD6AFD1EFC9B" author="Galiano" box="[493,651,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1997) Descripcion de Amphidraus argentinensis, nueva especie (Araneae, Salticidae). Physis Buenos Aires (C), 53, 33 - 36." type="journal article" year="1997">Galiano 1997</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 10). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99EABBFD6BFB92FC9B" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[903,1031,762,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulvinus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99EABBFD6BFB92FC9B" box="[903,1031,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. pulvinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF96FF99ED2CFD6AFBF9FC9B" box="[1040,1132,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99ED2CFD6AFBF9FC9B" bold="true" box="[1040,1132,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has RvTA and ITA bladeshaped, and a RTA linked to a pillow-like membrane (black arrows in 
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99EA9FFC8EFC7DFCBF" box="[931,1000,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,212,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1393,193,1791]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Amphidraus pulvinus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; ITA, intermediate tibial apopHysis; RSDL, retrolateral sperm duct loop; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. Black arrows indicate pillow-like membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855457/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Figs 8</figureCitation>
B, 8D), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99ED83FC8FFAE6FCBE" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1997" box="[1215,1395,799,822]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinensis">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99ED83FC8FFAE6FCBE" box="[1215,1395,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. argentinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the RvTA is trapezoidal with three apical teeth, and both the ITA and the pillow-like membrane are absent (see 
<bibRefCitation id="CA3D4B7EFF96FF99EC78FCD2FF46FCF7" author="Galiano" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1997) Descripcion de Amphidraus argentinensis, nueva especie (Araneae, Salticidae). Physis Buenos Aires (C), 53, 33 - 36." type="journal article" year="1997">Galiano 1997</bibRefCitation>
: figs 8, 11). 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99E85CFCF6FDF3FCF7" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[352,614,870,895]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complexus">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99E85CFCF6FDF3FCF7" box="[352,614,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Amphidraus complexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the pillow-like membrane, but differs from 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF96FF99ED87FCF7FAAFFCF7" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1211,1338,870,895]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulvinus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99ED87FCF7FAAFFCF7" box="[1211,1338,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">A. pulvinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF96FF99EC7EFCF6FA09FCF7" box="[1346,1436,870,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99EC7EFCF6FA09FCF7" bold="true" box="[1346,1436,870,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having one less projection in the embolic disc and a different shape of the tibial apophyses (see 
<bibRefCitation id="CA3D4B7EFF96FF99EC0FFC1AFEC4FC4F" author="Zhang" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" refString="ZHang, J. X &amp; Maddison, W. P. (2015) Genera of euopHryine jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae), witH a combined molecularmorpHological pHylogeny. Zootaxa, 3938 (1), 1 - 147." type="journal article" year="2015">Zhang &amp; Maddison, 2015</bibRefCitation>
: figs 211, 212).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF96FF9BE9FBFC42FE0FFF38" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="412" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" type="description">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF96FF99E9FBFC42FAD3FB4B" blockId="9.[151,1437,546,1219]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99E9FBFC42FD5CFC63" bold="true" box="[199,713,978,1003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus id="7117882DFF96FF99E89EFC42FD9CFC63" box="[418,521,978,1003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode id="C8BDAE4AFF96FF99EB2BFC42FDF8FC63" box="[535,621,978,1003]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">MPEG</collectionCode>
32687).
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.55. Carapace 1.25 long, 0.84 wide and 0.65 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.67 long. Anterior eye row 0.87 wide, posterior 0.72 wide. Legs: 431 = 2. Length of leg I 1.90 (0.57 + 0.68 + 0.65); II 1.90 (0.57 + 0.68 + 0.65); III 2.47 (0.72 + 0.84 + 0.91); IV 2.62 (0.76 + 0.87 + 0.99). Palp (
