<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99EA71FB16FC04FB17" box="[845,913,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,212,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1393,193,1791]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Amphidraus pulvinus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; ITA, intermediate tibial apopHysis; RSDL, retrolateral sperm duct loop; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. Black arrows indicate pillow-like membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855457/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
